 106     def test_conv_read_write(self, setup_path):
 107         path = create_tempfile(setup_path)
 108         try:
 109 
 110             def roundtrip(key, obj, **kwargs):
 111                 obj.to_hdf(path, key, **kwargs)
 112                 return read_hdf(path, key)
 113 
 114             o = tm.makeTimeSeries()
 115             tm.assert_series_equal(o, roundtrip("series", o))
 116 
 117             o = tm.makeStringSeries()
 118             tm.assert_series_equal(o, roundtrip("string_series", o))
 119 
 120             o = tm.makeDataFrame()
 121             tm.assert_frame_equal(o, roundtrip("frame", o))
 122 
 123             # table
 124             df = DataFrame(dict(A=range(5), B=range(5)))
 125             df.to_hdf(path, "table", append=True)
 126             result = read_hdf(path, "table", where=["index>2"])
 127             tm.assert_frame_equal(df[df.index > 2], result)
 128 
 129         finally:
 130             safe_remove(path)

 145     def test_api(self, setup_path):
 146 
 147         # GH4584
 148         # API issue when to_hdf doesn't accept append AND format args
 149         with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 150 
 151             df = tm.makeDataFrame()
 152             df.iloc[:10].to_hdf(path, "df", append=True, format="table")
 153             df.iloc[10:].to_hdf(path, "df", append=True, format="table")
 154             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)
 155 
 156             # append to False
 157             df.iloc[:10].to_hdf(path, "df", append=False, format="table")
 158             df.iloc[10:].to_hdf(path, "df", append=True, format="table")
 159             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)

 162 
 163             df = tm.makeDataFrame()
 164             df.iloc[:10].to_hdf(path, "df", append=True)
 165             df.iloc[10:].to_hdf(path, "df", append=True, format="table")
 166             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)
 167 
 168             # append to False
 169             df.iloc[:10].to_hdf(path, "df", append=False, format="table")
 170             df.iloc[10:].to_hdf(path, "df", append=True)
 171             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)
 172 
 173         with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 174 
 175             df = tm.makeDataFrame()
 176             df.to_hdf(path, "df", append=False, format="fixed")
 177             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)
 178 
 179             df.to_hdf(path, "df", append=False, format="f")
 180             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)
 181 
 182             df.to_hdf(path, "df", append=False)
 183             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)
 184 
 185             df.to_hdf(path, "df")
 186             tm.assert_frame_equal(read_hdf(path, "df"), df)
 187 
 188         with ensure_clean_store(setup_path) as store:
 189 
 190             path = store._path
 191             df = tm.makeDataFrame()
 192 
 193             _maybe_remove(store, "df")
 194             store.append("df", df.iloc[:10], append=True, format="table")
 195             store.append("df", df.iloc[10:], append=True, format="table")
 196             tm.assert_frame_equal(store.select("df"), df)

 199             _maybe_remove(store, "df")
 200             store.append("df", df.iloc[:10], append=False, format="table")
 201             store.append("df", df.iloc[10:], append=True, format="table")
 202             tm.assert_frame_equal(store.select("df"), df)
 203 
 204             # formats
 205             _maybe_remove(store, "df")
 206             store.append("df", df.iloc[:10], append=False, format="table")
 207             store.append("df", df.iloc[10:], append=True, format="table")
 208             tm.assert_frame_equal(store.select("df"), df)
 209 
 210             _maybe_remove(store, "df")
 211             store.append("df", df.iloc[:10], append=False, format="table")
 212             store.append("df", df.iloc[10:], append=True, format=None)
 213             tm.assert_frame_equal(store.select("df"), df)
 214 
 215         with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 216             # Invalid.
 217             df = tm.makeDataFrame()

 221             with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):

 242     def test_api_default_format(self, setup_path):
 243 
 244         # default_format option
 245         with ensure_clean_store(setup_path) as store:
 246             df = tm.makeDataFrame()
 247 
 248             pd.set_option("io.hdf.default_format", "fixed")
 249             _maybe_remove(store, "df")
 250             store.put("df", df)
 251             assert not store.get_storer("df").is_table
 252 
 253             msg = "Can only append to Tables"
 254 
 255             with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 256                 store.append("df2", df)
 257 
 258             pd.set_option("io.hdf.default_format", "table")
 259             _maybe_remove(store, "df")
 260             store.put("df", df)
 261             assert store.get_storer("df").is_table
 262             _maybe_remove(store, "df2")
 263             store.append("df2", df)
 264             assert store.get_storer("df").is_table
 265 
 266             pd.set_option("io.hdf.default_format", None)
 267 
 268         with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 269 
 270             df = tm.makeDataFrame()
 271 
 272             pd.set_option("io.hdf.default_format", "fixed")
 273             df.to_hdf(path, "df")
 274             with HDFStore(path) as store:
 275                 assert not store.get_storer("df").is_table
 276             with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 277                 df.to_hdf(path, "df2", append=True)
 278 
 279             pd.set_option("io.hdf.default_format", "table")
 280             df.to_hdf(path, "df3")
 281             with HDFStore(path) as store:
 282                 assert store.get_storer("df3").is_table
 283             df.to_hdf(path, "df4", append=True)
 284             with HDFStore(path) as store:
 285                 assert store.get_storer("df4").is_table
 286 
 287             pd.set_option("io.hdf.default_format", None)

 301     def test_no_track_times(self, setup_path):
 302 
 303         # GH 32682
 304         # enables to set track_times (see `pytables` `create_table` documentation)
 305 
 306         def checksum(filename, hash_factory=hashlib.md5, chunk_num_blocks=128):
 307             h = hash_factory()
 308             with open(filename, "rb") as f:
 309                 for chunk in iter(lambda: f.read(chunk_num_blocks * h.block_size), b""):
 310                     h.update(chunk)
 311             return h.digest()
 312 
 313         def create_h5_and_return_checksum(track_times):
 314             with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 315                 df = pd.DataFrame({"a": [1]})
 316 
 317                 with pd.HDFStore(path, mode="w") as hdf:
 318                     hdf.put(
 319                         "table",
 320                         df,
 321                         format="table",
 322                         data_columns=True,
 323                         index=None,
 324                         track_times=track_times,
 325                     )
 326 
 327                 return checksum(path)
 328 
 329         checksum_0_tt_false = create_h5_and_return_checksum(track_times=False)
 330         checksum_0_tt_true = create_h5_and_return_checksum(track_times=True)
 331 
 332         # sleep is necessary to create h5 with different creation time
 333         time.sleep(1)
 334 
 335         checksum_1_tt_false = create_h5_and_return_checksum(track_times=False)
 336         checksum_1_tt_true = create_h5_and_return_checksum(track_times=True)
 337 
 338         # checksums are the same if track_time = False
 339         assert checksum_0_tt_false == checksum_1_tt_false
 340 
 341         # checksums are NOT same if track_time = True
 342         assert checksum_0_tt_true != checksum_1_tt_true

 344     def test_non_pandas_keys(self, setup_path):
 345         class Table1(tables.IsDescription):
 346             value1 = tables.Float32Col()
 347 
 348         class Table2(tables.IsDescription):
 349             value2 = tables.Float32Col()
 350 
 351         class Table3(tables.IsDescription):
 352             value3 = tables.Float32Col()
 353 
 354         with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 355             with tables.open_file(path, mode="w") as h5file:
 356                 group = h5file.create_group("/", "group")
 357                 h5file.create_table(group, "table1", Table1, "Table 1")
 358                 h5file.create_table(group, "table2", Table2, "Table 2")
 359                 h5file.create_table(group, "table3", Table3, "Table 3")
 360             with HDFStore(path) as store:
 361                 assert len(store.keys(include="native")) == 3
 362                 expected = {"/group/table1", "/group/table2", "/group/table3"}
 363                 assert set(store.keys(include="native")) == expected
 364                 assert set(store.keys(include="pandas")) == set()
 365                 for name in expected:
 366                     df = store.get(name)
 367                     assert len(df.columns) == 1

 501                 if mode in ["r", "r+"]:
 502                     with pytest.raises(IOError):
 503                         HDFStore(path, mode=mode)
 504 
 505                 else:
 506                     store = HDFStore(path, mode=mode)
 507                     assert store._handle.mode == mode
 508                     store.close()
 509 
 510             with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 511 
 512                 # context
 513                 if mode in ["r", "r+"]:
 514                     with pytest.raises(IOError):
 515                         with HDFStore(path, mode=mode) as store:  # noqa
 516                             pass
 517                 else:
 518                     with HDFStore(path, mode=mode) as store:
 519                         assert store._handle.mode == mode
 520 
 521             with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 522 
 523                 # conv write
 524                 if mode in ["r", "r+"]:
 525                     with pytest.raises(IOError):
 526                         df.to_hdf(path, "df", mode=mode)
 527                     df.to_hdf(path, "df", mode="w")
 528                 else:
 529                     df.to_hdf(path, "df", mode=mode)
 530 
 531                 # conv read
 532                 if mode in ["w"]:
 533                     msg = (
 534                         "mode w is not allowed while performing a read. "
 535                         r"Allowed modes are r, r\+ and a."
 536                     )
 537                     with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=msg):
 538                         read_hdf(path, "df", mode=mode)
 539                 else:
 540                     result = read_hdf(path, "df", mode=mode)
 541                     tm.assert_frame_equal(result, df)
 542 
 543         def check_default_mode():
 544 
 545             # read_hdf uses default mode
 546             with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 547                 df.to_hdf(path, "df", mode="w")
 548                 result = read_hdf(path, "df")
 549                 tm.assert_frame_equal(result, df)
 550 
 551         check("r")
 552         check("r+")
 553         check("a")
 554         check("w")
 555         check_default_mode()

 557     def test_reopen_handle(self, setup_path):
 558 
 559         with ensure_clean_path(setup_path) as path:
 560 
 561             store = HDFStore(path, mode="a")
 562             store["a"] = tm.makeTimeSeries()
 563 
 564             # invalid mode change
 565             with pytest.raises(PossibleDataLossError):
 566                 store.open("w")
 567 
 568             store.close()
 569             assert not store.is_open
 570 
 571             # truncation ok here
 572             store.open("w")
 573             assert store.is_open
 574             assert len(store) == 0
 575             store.close()
 576             assert not store.is_open
 577 
 578             store = HDFStore(path, mode="a")
 579             store["a"] = tm.makeTimeSeries()
 580 
 581             # reopen as read
 582             store.open("r")
 583             assert store.is_open
 584             assert len(store) == 1
 585             assert store._mode == "r"
 586             store.close()
 587             assert not store.is_open
 588 
 589             # reopen as append
 590             store.open("a")
 591             assert store.is_open
 592             assert len(store) == 1
 593             assert store._mode == "a"
 594             store.close()
 595             assert not store.is_open
 596 
 597             # reopen as append (again)
 598             store.open("a")
 599             assert store.is_open
 600             assert len(store) == 1
 601             assert store._mode == "a"
 602             store.close()
 603             assert not store.is_open

 648     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 649         "where, expected",
 650         [
 651             (
 652                 "/",
 653                 {
 654                     "": ({"first_group", "second_group"}, set()),
 655                     "/first_group": (set(), {"df1", "df2"}),
 656                     "/second_group": ({"third_group"}, {"df3", "s1"}),
 657                     "/second_group/third_group": (set(), {"df4"}),
 658                 },
 659             ),
 660             (

 669     def test_walk(self, where, expected, setup_path):
 670         # GH10143
 671         objs = {
 672             "df1": pd.DataFrame([1, 2, 3]),
 673             "df2": pd.DataFrame([4, 5, 6]),
 674             "df3": pd.DataFrame([6, 7, 8]),
 675             "df4": pd.DataFrame([9, 10, 11]),
 676             "s1": pd.Series([10, 9, 8]),
 677             # Next 3 items aren't pandas objects and should be ignored
 678             "a1": np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]]),
 679             "tb1": np.array([(1, 2, 3), (4, 5, 6)], dtype="i,i,i"),
 680             "tb2": np.array([(7, 8, 9), (10, 11, 12)], dtype="i,i,i"),
 681         }
 682 
 683         with ensure_clean_store("walk_groups.hdf", mode="w") as store:
 684             store.put("/first_group/df1", objs["df1"])
 685             store.put("/first_group/df2", objs["df2"])
 686             store.put("/second_group/df3", objs["df3"])
 687             store.put("/second_group/s1", objs["s1"])
 688             store.put("/second_group/third_group/df4", objs["df4"])
 689             # Create non-pandas objects
 690             store._handle.create_array("/first_group", "a1", objs["a1"])
 691             store._handle.create_table("/first_group", "tb1", obj=objs["tb1"])
 692             store._handle.create_table("/second_group", "tb2", obj=objs["tb2"])
 693 
 694             assert len(list(store.walk(where=where))) == len(expected)
 695             for path, groups, leaves in store.walk(where=where):
 696                 assert path in expected
 697                 expected_groups, expected_frames = expected[path]
 698                 assert expected_groups == set(groups)
 699                 assert expected_frames == set(leaves)
 700                 for leaf in leaves:
 701                     frame_path = "/".join([path, leaf])
 702                     obj = store.get(frame_path)
 703                     if "df" in leaf:
 704                         tm.assert_frame_equal(obj, objs[leaf])
 705                     else:
 706                         tm.assert_series_equal(obj, objs[leaf])

1333     def test_append_with_different_block_ordering(self, setup_path):
1334 
1335         # GH 4096; using same frames, but different block orderings
1336         with ensure_clean_store(setup_path) as store:
1337 
1338             for i in range(10):
1339 
1340                 df = DataFrame(np.random.randn(10, 2), columns=list("AB"))
1341                 df["index"] = range(10)
1342                 df["index"] += i * 10
1343                 df["int64"] = Series([1] * len(df), dtype="int64")
1344                 df["int16"] = Series([1] * len(df), dtype="int16")
1345 
1346                 if i % 2 == 0:
1347                     del df["int64"]
1348                     df["int64"] = Series([1] * len(df), dtype="int64")
1349                 if i % 3 == 0:
1350                     a = df.pop("A")
1351                     df["A"] = a
1352 
1353                 df.set_index("index", inplace=True)
1354 
1355                 store.append("df", df)

1357         # test a different ordering but with more fields (like invalid
1358         # combinate)
1359         with ensure_clean_store(setup_path) as store:
1360 
1361             df = DataFrame(np.random.randn(10, 2), columns=list("AB"), dtype="float64")
1362             df["int64"] = Series([1] * len(df), dtype="int64")
1363             df["int16"] = Series([1] * len(df), dtype="int16")
1364             store.append("df", df)
1365 
1366             # store additional fields in different blocks
1367             df["int16_2"] = Series([1] * len(df), dtype="int16")
1368             with pytest.raises(ValueError):
1369                 store.append("df", df)
1370 
1371             # store multiple additional fields in different blocks

1373             with pytest.raises(ValueError):
1374                 store.append("df", df)

3280     def test_frame_select_complex(self, setup_path):
3281         # select via complex criteria
3282 
3283         df = tm.makeTimeDataFrame()
3284         df["string"] = "foo"
3285         df.loc[df.index[0:4], "string"] = "bar"
3286 
3287         with ensure_clean_store(setup_path) as store:
3288             store.put("df", df, format="table", data_columns=["string"])
3289 
3290             # empty
3291             result = store.select("df", 'index>df.index[3] & string="bar"')
3292             expected = df.loc[(df.index > df.index[3]) & (df.string == "bar")]
3293             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)
3294 
3295             result = store.select("df", 'index>df.index[3] & string="foo"')
3296             expected = df.loc[(df.index > df.index[3]) & (df.string == "foo")]
3297             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)
3298 
3299             # or
3300             result = store.select("df", 'index>df.index[3] | string="bar"')
3301             expected = df.loc[(df.index > df.index[3]) | (df.string == "bar")]
3302             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)
3303 
3304             result = store.select(
3305                 "df", '(index>df.index[3] & index<=df.index[6]) | string="bar"'
3306             )
3307             expected = df.loc[
3308                 ((df.index > df.index[3]) & (df.index <= df.index[6]))
3309                 | (df.string == "bar")
3310             ]
3311             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)
3312 
3313             # invert
3314             result = store.select("df", 'string!="bar"')
3315             expected = df.loc[df.string != "bar"]
3316             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)
3317 
3318             # invert not implemented in numexpr :(
3319             with pytest.raises(NotImplementedError):
3320                 store.select("df", '~(string="bar")')
3321 
3322             # invert ok for filters
3323             result = store.select("df", "~(columns=['A','B'])")
3324             expected = df.loc[:, df.columns.difference(["A", "B"])]
3325             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)
3326 
3327             # in
3328             result = store.select("df", "index>df.index[3] & columns in ['A','B']")
3329             expected = df.loc[df.index > df.index[3]].reindex(columns=["A", "B"])
3330             tm.assert_frame_equal(result, expected)

3943     def _check_roundtrip(self, obj, comparator, path, compression=False, **kwargs):
3944 
3945         options = {}
3946         if compression:
3947             options["complib"] = _default_compressor
3948 
3949         with ensure_clean_store(path, "w", **options) as store:
3950             store["obj"] = obj
3951             retrieved = store["obj"]
3952             comparator(retrieved, obj, **kwargs)
3953 
3954     def _check_double_roundtrip(
3955         self, obj, comparator, path, compression=False, **kwargs
3956     ):
3957         options = {}
3958         if compression:
3959             options["complib"] = compression or _default_compressor
3960 
3961         with ensure_clean_store(path, "w", **options) as store:
3962             store["obj"] = obj
3963             retrieved = store["obj"]
3964             comparator(retrieved, obj, **kwargs)
3965             store["obj"] = retrieved
3966             again = store["obj"]
3967             comparator(again, obj, **kwargs)
3968 
3969     def _check_roundtrip_table(self, obj, comparator, path, compression=False):

3971         if compression:
3972             options["complib"] = _default_compressor
3973 
3974         with ensure_clean_store(path, "w", **options) as store:
3975             store.put("obj", obj, format="table")
3976             retrieved = store["obj"]
3977 
3978             comparator(retrieved, obj)

4162     def test_copy(self, setup_path):
4163 
4164         with catch_warnings(record=True):
4165 
4166             def do_copy(f, new_f=None, keys=None, propindexes=True, **kwargs):
4167                 try:
4168                     store = HDFStore(f, "r")
4169 
4170                     if new_f is None:
4171                         import tempfile
4172 
4173                         fd, new_f = tempfile.mkstemp()
4174 
4175                     tstore = store.copy(
4176                         new_f, keys=keys, propindexes=propindexes, **kwargs
4177                     )
4178 
4179                     # check keys
4180                     if keys is None:
4181                         keys = store.keys()
4182                     assert set(keys) == set(tstore.keys())
4183 
4184                     # check indices & nrows
4185                     for k in tstore.keys():
4186                         if tstore.get_storer(k).is_table:
4187                             new_t = tstore.get_storer(k)
4188                             orig_t = store.get_storer(k)
4189 
4190                             assert orig_t.nrows == new_t.nrows
4191 
4192                             # check propindixes
4193                             if propindexes:
4194                                 for a in orig_t.axes:
4195                                     if a.is_indexed:
4196                                         assert new_t[a.name].is_indexed
4197 
4198                 finally:
4199                     safe_close(store)
4200                     safe_close(tstore)
4201                     try:
4202                         os.close(fd)
4203                     except (OSError, ValueError):
4204                         pass
4205                     safe_remove(new_f)
4206 
4207             # new table
4208             df = tm.makeDataFrame()
4209 
4210             try:
4211                 path = create_tempfile(setup_path)
4212                 st = HDFStore(path)
4213                 st.append("df", df, data_columns=["A"])
4214                 st.close()
4215                 do_copy(f=path)
4216                 do_copy(f=path, propindexes=False)
4217             finally:
4218                 safe_remove(path)

4751     def test_query_compare_column_type(self, setup_path):
4752         # GH 15492
4753         df = pd.DataFrame(
4754             {
4755                 "date": ["2014-01-01", "2014-01-02"],
4756                 "real_date": date_range("2014-01-01", periods=2),
4757                 "float": [1.1, 1.2],
4758                 "int": [1, 2],
4759             },
4760             columns=["date", "real_date", "float", "int"],
4761         )
4762 
4763         with ensure_clean_store(setup_path) as store:
4764             store.append("test", df, format="table", data_columns=True)
4765 
4766             ts = pd.Timestamp("2014-01-01")  # noqa
4767             result = store.select("test", where="real_date > ts")
4768             expected = df.loc[[1], :]
4769             tm.assert_frame_equal(expected, result)
4770 
4771             for op in ["<", ">", "=="]:
4772                 # non strings to string column always fail
4773                 for v in [2.1, True, pd.Timestamp("2014-01-01"), pd.Timedelta(1, "s")]:
4774                     query = f"date {op} v"
4775                     with pytest.raises(TypeError):
4776                         store.select("test", where=query)
4777 
4778                 # strings to other columns must be convertible to type
4779                 v = "a"
4780                 for col in ["int", "float", "real_date"]:
4781                     query = f"{col} {op} v"
4782                     with pytest.raises(ValueError):
4783                         store.select("test", where=query)
4784 
4785                 for v, col in zip(
4786                     ["1", "1.1", "2014-01-01"], ["int", "float", "real_date"]
4787                 ):
4788                     query = f"{col} {op} v"
4789                     result = store.select("test", where=query)
4790 
4791                     if op == "==":
4792                         expected = df.loc[[0], :]
4793                     elif op == ">":
4794                         expected = df.loc[[1], :]
4795                     else:
4796                         expected = df.loc[[], :]
4797                     tm.assert_frame_equal(expected, result)
